about.summary: The 'LabKey' client library for R makes it easy for R users to load live data from a 'LabKey' Server, <http://www.labkey.com/>, into the R environment for analysis, provided users have permissions to read the data. It also enables R users to insert, update, and delete records stored on a 'LabKey' Server, provided they have appropriate permissions to do so.

name: r-rlabkey
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.3.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rlabkey
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Rlabkey_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/Rlabkey/Rlabkey_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a5402ea390e8bef69940ad37279e67dd85565cd885510d7ab218b191aa9e5192

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.0
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp >=0.11.0
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('Rlabkey')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('Rlabkey')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=Rlabkey
  license: Apache 2.0
  summary: The 'LabKey' client library for R makes it easy for R users to load live data from
    a 'LabKey' Server, <http://www.labkey.com/>, into the R environment for analysis,
    provided users have permissions to read the data. It also enables R users to insert,
    update, and delete records stored on a 'LabKey' Server, provided they have appropriate
    permissions to do so.
  license_family: APACHE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
